**Wolfhart Pannenberg: A German Theologian of Revelation and History**

- Wolfhart Pannenberg is a Protestant theologian who argues that God reveals himself through his actions in history, especially in the life, death, and resurrection of Jesus Christ.
- He was born on 2nd October 1928 and died on 4th September 2014
- He develops his idea of revelation as history in his work Jesus – God and Man (1968), where he claims that the resurrection of Christ is the key to interpreting history.
- He also explores questions of theological method and the relation between theology and the natural sciences in his works Theology and the Philosophy of Science (1977) and Systematic Theology (1988–93).
